 over $x\\in\\mathbb{R}^d$. We show that sketching\ndimension $O(\\log(d)/(\\lambda \\varepsilon)^2)$ suffices and that the dependence\non $d$ and $\\lambda$ is tight.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Apr 2023 07:24:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-06"}
